    ],
    "diagnosis_confidence": "High",
    "diagnosis_explanation": "The get_network_status tool reported that the 'dns' container has 'exited'. DNS is critical for an IMS network, as all routing and service discovery is based on Fully Qualified Domain Names (FQDNs) like 'pcscf.ims.mnc001.mcc001.3gppnetwork.org'. While some components might be configured with static IPs, UEs and other components rely on DNS to initiate connections. The errors at the I-CSCF are a secondary symptom; even if it could talk to the HSS via IP, it would be unable to route the call to the correct S-CSCF without DNS. The existing registrations are likely stale, from a time when DNS was working.",
